/*
:name: reserved_word_signal
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: top
:pyrope_top: reserved_word_signal.top
*/

// FAILING regression for 2i-issues F: cgen must escape SystemVerilog-2012
// reserved words used as signal names. `packed` is an IEEE-1800 keyword. cgen's
// get_scaped_name (inou/cgen/cgen_verilog.cpp:87-100 / :174) only escapes ~14
// classic Verilog-2001 keywords, so it emits a BARE `output ... packed`, which
// yosys (unexpected TOK_PACKED), iverilog -g2012, and verilator all reject.
//
// This is purely combinational (no register) to isolate the cgen emission bug.
// The `:type: equiv` harness re-reads the GENERATED verilog through lgcheck/
// yosys, so this test is RED until cgen emits `\packed ` (escaped). Fix is to
// extend the reserved_keyword set with the IEEE-1800 additions (packed, bit,
// byte, int, shortint, longint, void, type, ref, return, automatic, static,
// unique, priority, interface, modport, package, program, time, real).
pub comb top(a:u8) -> (packed:u8) {
  packed = a + 1
}
